  IMAP &ConfigureOptions;




     &Name;
     &Default;
     &Changeable;
     &Changelog;





     imap.enable_insecure_rsh
     "0"
     PHP_INI_SYSTEM
     Available as of PHP 7.1.25, 7.2.13 and 7.3.0. Formerly, it was implicitly enabled.





 &ini.php.constants;



&ini.descriptions.title;







    imap.enable_insecure_rsh
    bool




     Establishing a connection to a server may invoke rsh or
     ssh commands, unless this &php.ini; option is disabled.



      Neither PHP nor the IMAP library filter
      mailbox names before passing them to rsh or ssh
      commands, thus passing untrusted data to this function without disabling this
      &php.ini; option is insecure.
